column1: How many forecasters will join the Global Judgment Challenge on Good Judgment Open before 8 January, 2018?
column5: ['Fewer than 1,000', 'Between 1,000 and 2,000, inclusive', 'More than 2,000 but fewer than 3,000 ', 'Between 3,000 and 4,000, inclusive', 'More than 4,000']
column6: ['Entertainment']
column11: Good Judgment Open's Global Judgment Challenge, sponsored by CNN's "Fareed Zakaria GPS," will be featured on the program twice, on 31 December 2017 and 7 January 2018 (Global Judgment Challenge, Fareed Zakaria GPS). "Fareed Zakaria GPS" was the second most popular cable news show on weekends in Q3 2017 (AdWeek) Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: the power of mass media!
Having Fareed as a spokes person for this challenge, will be a big hit, thus many many signing up.

Hunkering down for the surge. As of 8:30 am PST, need 767 to get over 3,000. That's about 70% of the first show.
Sounds about right
With only a few hours left, there are currently approx 2200 participants.

Surge time!

https://www.gjopen.com/memberships/28414/forecast_history

It has been outlined before. The probability to enroll many new members is low. There`s still the possibility of a black swan event, but given that the promotional machine is running since quite a while (I assume that there no hidden sign up incentive offered today or tomorrow - would enter the category of manipulation) and I couldn´t find any incentives offered to join until Jan 08 and not later, it would be extraordinarily odd to surpass the 3000 threshold.
instinct guess

2090 at 1:20 AM EST on 6 Jan 2018. 131 in past 41 hours, or 77 per 24 hours. One more day at this rate will take us to approx. 2167. Will we get 833 or more new forecasters on 7 January? Hmmmm.
@dsarin regarding the surge... you make a really good point to not assume a lessor surge. And @tsm -- the allure of the beautiful bridges make it hard to resist. Hedging a little.

For your imagination,

I'm winding down on a daily basis to about 25/day but do wonder about the Sunday effect which I'm guessing @half of the original 1,100 so adding about 600 to a 25/day daily = which equals around 2,700 But if the Sunday show adds more like 900 to that -- then it equals around 2,940 And there is that social media ad effect as well = ? Watching for the Sunday (2 shows effect). Is it half (550), or two thirds, or is it the same as the first Sunday effect (1,100) ? that could bring the total to over 3,000. Not sure. I'm guessing that it's less than the first Sunday surge but either way, the total is really close.

Even with a surge of participants, the window is too small considering the number of current participants since the open. The forecast over the next 4 days makes it unlikely that there will be a significant enough of an uptick in participants.

OK. Ready for a flutter now. Especially so as this question does not appear to be associated with any particular challenge, so we do not appear to have Accuracy points on the line that might sabotage our rankings in other challenges. Most useful references have been those provided by @amory10 and @praedico in this thread: https://www.gjopen.com/comments/comments/652299.
The sign-up procedures are pretty laborious, There will probably be many who check it out but abandon the effort before completing the survey and actually getting in.
Base rate: Opened Dec. 15th, 380 forecasters in 15 days is approx. 25 per day. Base rate extrapolation: 8 additional days @ 25 / day is another 200 after Jan. 7th, 580 total.
Alternate Q: Which challenge will gain the most forecasters before 1/8?

So as of 30DEC17 there are a few challenges closing. These make for good comps; 1764, 2694, 1682, 4483, 6158. Making a quick analysis we throw out the high and the low to get 1764, 2694, 4483 Summed= 8941 then divide by 3 = 2980 which just says what a typical challenge should do after 1 year. However, is this case different? Yes. There are only 384 forecasters at this time. Best guess would be to make the 2980 an upper limit.
Now here's a question we have some control over. Join up!
